The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Whirlpool plan
                                                                                                               Whirlpool plan
          A STAFF REPORTER                          Das Gupta in Calcutta on Saturday. A Telegraph picture                                  
	Calcutta, Jan. 24: Whirlpool of India plans to increase its share in the home appliances segment to over 20 per cent by December from its current 16 per cent.         
	The company will invest about Rs 120 crore ($30 billion) during the period in product development, besides the Rs 60-70 crore spent every year on promotions.        
	Our growth strategy this year would be to strengthen our core segments  refrigerators and washing machines, vice-president (marketing) Shantanu Das Gupta said.         
	The company today launched a range of fully automatic washing machines in the 6 to 8 kg category.         
	An investment of $4 million went into developing the new range, especially in setting up a new production line at its Pondicherry plant to produce some of the higher capacity models.                                                                                                                                        
